Data Visualization in rrr

Chris Addy

2016-12-06

The Philosophy of Graphics in rrr

The graphical display of data should be intuitive enough that any viewer of the display unfamiliar with the data, even unfamiliar with statistical analysis generally, should be able to see clear patterns, if in fact clear patterns exist in the data. This, the author believes, is especially true for multivariate data, where due to the higher dimensionality of the data, the potential for visualization to overwhelm is high.

library(dplyr)

### LOAD DATA

### TOBACCO DATA SET
data(tobacco)

tobacco_x <- tobacco %>%
    select(starts_with("X"))

tobacco_y <- tobacco %>% 
    select(starts_with("Y"))

### PENDIGITS DATA SET
data(pendigits)
digits <- as_data_frame(pendigits)

digits_class <- digits %>% select(V35)
digits_features <- digits %>% select(-V35, -V36)

### COMBO-17 GALAXY DATA SET
data(COMBO17)
galaxy <- as_data_frame(COMBO17) %>%
       select(-starts_with("e."), -Nr, -UFS:-IFD) %>%
       na.omit()

### IRIS DATA SET
data(iris)
iris <- as_data_frame(iris)

iris_features <- iris %>%
    select(-Species)

iris_class <- iris %>%
    select(Species)

### COMBO-17 DATA SET
data(COMBO17)
galaxy <- as_data_frame(COMBO17) %>%
       select(-starts_with("e."), -Nr, -UFS:-IFD) %>%
       na.omit()

galaxy_x <- galaxy %>%
    select(-Rmag:-chi2red)

galaxy_y <- galaxy %>%
    select(Rmag:chi2red)
pca_rank_trace(digits_features)

pca_pairwise_plot(digits_features)

pca_pairwise_plot(digits_features, pc_x = 1, pc_y = 3, class_labels = digits_class)

Rank Trace Plots

gamma1 <- diag(1, 3)
gamma2 <- solve(cov(tobacco_y))

rank_trace(tobacco_x, tobacco_y, gamma1)

rank_trace(tobacco_x, tobacco_y, gamma2)

Rank trace plots can be made interactive with the argument interactive = TRUE.

rank_trace(tobacco_x, tobacco_y, gamma1, interactive = TRUE)
rank_trace(tobacco_x, tobacco_y, gamma2, interactive = TRUE)

RRR Residuals Plots

#rrr_residuals_plot(tobacco_x, tobacco_y, ident, rank = 1)

PC Rank Trace Plots

pca_rank_trace(digits_features)

PCA rank trace plots can be made interactive with the argument interactive = TRUE.

pca_rank_trace(digits_features, interactive = TRUE)

PC Pairwise Plots

pca_pairwise_plot(digits_features, pc_x = 1, pc_y = 3, class_labels = digits_class, interactive = TRUE)

PCA 3D Plots

pca_3D_plot(digits_features, class_labels = digits_class)
## Warning in RColorBrewer::brewer.pal(N, "Set2"): n too large, allowed maximum for palette Set2 is 8

Change Point Size with argument point_size

pca_3D_plot(iris_features, class_labels = iris_class)
pca_3D_plot(iris_features, class_labels = iris_class, point_size = 5)

CVA Rank Trace Plots

cva_rank_trace(galaxy_x, galaxy_y)

cva_rank_trace(galaxy_x, galaxy_y, interactive = TRUE)

CVA Pairwise Plots

cva_pairwise_plot(galaxy_x, galaxy_y, cv_pair = 2)

cva_pairwise_plot(galaxy_x, galaxy_y, cv_pair = 2, interactive = TRUE)

CVA Residuals Plots

cva_residual_plot(galaxy_x, galaxy_y, rank = 2)

cva_residual_plot(galaxy_x, galaxy_y, rank = 2, interactive = TRUE)

CVA 3D Residuals Plots

cva_residual_3D_plot(galaxy_x, galaxy_y)

LDA Pairwise Plots

lda_pairwise_plot(iris_features, iris_class)

lda_pairwise_plot(iris_features, iris_class, interactive = TRUE)

LDA 3D Plots
